# chat

Interactive terminal REPL front-end — the Claude-CLI-style daily driver.
Additive: reuses `run_single` / the tool surface / the prompt registry
unchanged. The deterministic benchmark path (`luxe maintain`, `benchmarks/`)
never touches this module.

## Must
- Every user turn drives exactly ONE `run_single()` call; conversation state
  lives in `ChatSession`, folded into `goal=` + a tagged `extra_context` block —
  never by forking `run_agent`'s message loop or changing its signature
- Context precedence (highest wins): current user turn > project memory >
  conversation summary. `extra_context` is tagged `<project_memory>` /
  `<conversation_history>` / `<current_request>` so history can't read as commands
- Default slot config = champion in chat/plan/code (`model_for_slot` returns the
  monolith model when `slots` is None or `model_key=""`); byte-identical model
  selection to `single_64gb.yaml`
- Multi-slot fan-out activates ONLY on explicit `configs/chat.yaml` `slots:` —
  the sanctioned, opt-in exception to luxe.sdd "no per-task model selection",
  scoped to this front-end
- Slot routing is visible: the render footer shows the fired slot + model every
  turn; `/use <slot>` and `/model <slot> <id>` are explicit user overrides
- Different-model slot use sequences weight swaps via
  `Backend.unload_all_loaded` + `thermal_guard`; swap count + seconds are
  instrumented and surfaced; keep chat-slot model resident, group code work
- The history summarizer (`chat/summarize.py`) is NON-model, deterministic, and
  versioned (`SUMMARIZER_VERSION`); its output is persisted to `fold.jsonl`
- Ctrl-C during a turn aborts at the next tool boundary, persists the partial
  transcript, and returns to the prompt (no process exit)
- Write tools default OFF (read-only, reusing the `serve`/`make_read_only_role`
  precedent); `/write` toggles; write-mode is shown in the footer every turn
- In read-only mode a lowest-precedence `<session_mode>` block (string =
  `prompts.READ_ONLY_CHAT_HINT`, never inlined here) is injected so the model
  points the user at `/write` instead of claiming luxe can't create/edit files
- `/ctx <tier>` sets a per-session `num_ctx` override (small/medium/large/xlarge);
  it is CHAT-ONLY and always clamped to the role's `num_ctx_max` (config) so a
  request can never exceed what the box/model holds. `num_ctx_max: 0` (default)
  forbids any expansion. Resize is never silent — high context pressure only
  *suggests* the next tier; the user opts in. The benchmark/maintain path never
  reads `num_ctx_max` and is unaffected.
- `/bash` toggles unrestricted shell (default OFF = hardened allowlist). When ON
  AND write mode is on, the turn passes `unrestricted_bash_def()` +
  `make_bash_fn(unrestricted=True)` through `run_single`'s extra-tool seam,
  overriding the allowlisted bash for that run only. Effective only in write mode
  (bash is stripped in read-only). Visible on the slot line every turn. The
  benchmark/maintain path passes no extra tools, so its bash stays allowlisted.
- `luxe chat --dev` starts with write + unrestricted bash ON (sticky equivalent
  of `/write` + `/bash`), so dev work doesn't re-toggle each session
- Defaults stay safe (read-only + allowlisted bash) but the state must be VISIBLE
  and flag-gated failures must be SELF-EXPLAINING: write mode (non-dev) injects
  `restricted_bash_def()` + `make_bash_fn(restricted_hint=True)` so an
  allowlist/chain/substitution rejection front-loads "enable unrestricted dev mode
  with /bash" onto the error (survives the 80-char tool-line truncation) and the
  def tells the model to surface the flag rather than retry. Genuine errors
  (mismatched quotes, timeouts, non-zero exit) are NOT augmented. The startup
  banner names the initial mode + toggles; the status-bar chips show live state.
- The status bar (`chat/status.py`) order (user spec):
  `path · git · ctx · cache · start · last · write · bash · slot · model`.
  `ctx` = `ctx N% <window-size>` (size in the K/M context convention, e.g. 128K;
  the size shows immediately — seeded from the slot's role num_ctx at startup —
  and the % appears once a turn measures usage);
  `cache` = resident prompt size (luxe has no cross-turn prompt cache — each turn
  is a fresh `run_single`, so it's the prompt/KV size processed last turn, NOT an
  Anthropic-style cache); `write`/`bash` show explicit on/off; the luxe mode
  (slot, e.g. `chat`) is its own segment, then the model name pinned last. The
  startup banner is intentionally minimal (session + /help) — repo/slot/model/mode
  are NOT reprinted there since the bar already shows them. `fields()` (→ `list[Segment]`, each
  with a drop-`priority`) is the single source of order/content; `toolbar()`
  (prompt_toolkit bottom bar — its grey/reversed background is overridden to
  `bg:default` so the bar sits on the terminal background), `status_markup()`
  (plain-input fallback), and `to_rich_text()`/`LiveActivity` (in-turn live bar)
  all render from it so they never drift. `fit(segs, width)` is responsive: it
  drops low-value segments (cache=8, start/last=7) highest-first, then
  middle-ellipsises the elastic path; path/git/ctx/model (priority 1–2) protected.
  Git state is TTL-cached to avoid per-keystroke `git` spawns.
- Colours follow the user's ACTIVE Claude statusline theme, resolved LIVE by
  `chat/theme.py`: read the theme name (`CLAUDE_STATUSLINE_THEME` env →
  `~/.claude/statusline-theme` → `claude-dark`), import the user's
  yet-another-statusline `themes` module via the `~/.claude/statusline_command.py`
  symlink, and convert each role's ANSI escape to a (ptk, Rich) pair — ANSI 0-15
  → NAMED colours (track the iTerm2 profile), 16-255 → fixed xterm value,
  rgb/default pass through. The GIT segment is styled by theme ROLE
  (branch/commit/dirty/safe/warn/alert), cached per process; the rest use a
  sparing luxe palette per the user's spec: path BLUE (fixed hex — the terminal's
  ANSI-blue slot renders orange on the user's profile), luxe-mode/slot PURPLE,
  model name YELLOW, state on=GREEN/off=RED, `ctx`/`write`/`bash` LABEL words in
  terminal default fg ("white"/prominent — true white would vanish on the light
  bg), other labels + separators grey, values = default fg. Falls back to a
  built-in llmtop-equivalent ANSI map if the
  repo/symlink/import is absent. NOTE: this reads only the theme-name file and imports the user's pure
  themes module for COLOURS — it is NOT the memory subsystem and injects no
  `~/.claude` content into context (the luxe.sdd/chat.sdd `~/.claude` prohibition
  is scoped to context/memory, not UI theming).
- During a turn (when `console.is_terminal`) the REPL renders a `rich.Live`:
  tool tail-log scrolls above a status bar that ticks live (spinner/elapsed/tool
  count via `LiveActivity`, auto-refresh). Non-terminal (tests, piped) falls back
  to the `Status` spinner + line streaming — deterministic loop untouched either
  way. `transient=True` clears the in-turn bar; the footer prints below.

## Must not
- Modify `agents/loop.py`'s `backend.chat` call site or `run_agent` signature
  (preserves benchmark determinism)
- Introduce any system/task prompt strings here — those stay in
  `agents/prompts.py`. `extra_context` is runtime conversation framing, not a
  registry prompt
- Auto-open PRs from a chat turn (the PR cycle stays in `luxe maintain`/`luxe pr`)
- Let `configs/chat.yaml` change the behavior of `single_64gb.yaml` / maintain

## Owns
- src/luxe/chat/**
